				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Copper slag concentrate, often referred to as copper slag (CS), is an industrial byproduct obtained during the copper manufacturing process. It is produced in significant quantities from primary sources, with an estimated production of more than 45 million tonnes from a slag to copper ratio of 2.2. Copper slag waste has been extensively recycled and repurposed, particularly in cement and concrete production, to promote a circular economy and environmental benefits. However, only 15% of copper slag worldwide is used as a product, while the remainder is typically landfilled.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">铜渣精矿，通常称为铜渣（CS），是在铜冶炼过程中获得的工业副产品。它被认为是具有显着产出的高质量二次资源。铜渣的回收利用具有避免有价金属损失、减轻有害金属威胁、节约自然资源和能源的潜力，因此备受关注。铜渣废料已被广泛回收并重新用于水泥和混凝土生产，为循环经济做出了贡献</common:generalComment>
